File: There were concerns that about 10 players were at risk of being infected as they were part of the cancelled four-day domestic matches. Barco Greeff / AFP JOHANNESBURG - There's some great news coming from the Proteas camp, with all squad players cleared of COVID-19. There were concerns that about 10 players were at risk of being infected as they were part of the cancelled four-day domestic matches. READ: COVID-19 case forces postponement of Proteas, England ODI match But, all players received a clean bill of health ahead of the two Test Series against Sri Lanka which starts this week. The team enters the bio-bubble in Irene COVID-19-free and hoping to complete the scheduled tests. Recently, only three T20 matches were possible between South Africa and England, following several scares that resulted in the remainder of the tour being cancelled.